Source: libprolog
Section: libs
Priority: optional
Maintainer: Krisztian Litkey <krisztian.litkey@nokia.com>
Standards-Version: 0.0.1
Build-Depends: cdbs, debhelper (>= 4.1.0), swi-prolog

Package: libprolog
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, swi-prolog
Description: Prolog convenience library
 The Prolog convenience library contains a small set of functions that
 are supposed to make embedding the SWI-prolog interpreter easier.
 .
 The library also contains a set of SWI-prolog extensions used by our policy
 framework.

Package: prolog-extensions
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}, swi-prolog
Description: Prolog extensions for the policy framework
 A set of prolgo extensions needed by the policy framework (and/or its
 prototype implementation).

Package: libfact
Architecture: any
Section: libs
Depends: ${shlibs:Depends}
Description: Factstore library
 The factstore library provides a more featureful alternative to the
 OHM keystore. It is separated to a library of its own for easier
 integration to the dependency reolver and prolog extensions.

